analysis.info:
FEL-contrast (Fixed Effects Likelihood) investigates whether or not selective pressures differ between two or more sets of
    branches at a site. Site-specific synonymous (alpha) and non-synonymous (beta, one per branch set) substitution rates are estimated
    and then beta rates are tested for equality at each site. LRT is used to assess significance.
analysis.citation: Kosakovsky Pond SL, Frost SDW, Grossman Z, Gravenor MB, Richman DD, Leigh Brown AJ (2006) Adaptation to Different Human Populations by HIV-1 Revealed by Codon-Based Analyses. PLoS Comput Biol 2(6): e62.
analysis.requirements: in-frame codon alignment and a phylogenetic tree; only single partition data are supported

headers: alpha
Synonymous substitution rate at a site
beta (background)
Non-synonymous substitution rate at a site for background branches
beta (T_cells)
Non-synonymous substitution rate at a site for T_cells branches
beta (Plasma)
Non-synonymous substitution rate at a site for Plasma branches
beta (Monocytes)
Non-synonymous substitution rate at a site for Monocytes branches
p-value (overall)
P-value for the test that non-synonymous rates differ between any of the selected groups: T_cells,Plasma,Monocytes
P-value for T_cells vs Plasma
P-value for  the test that non-synonymous rates differ between T_cells and Plasma branches
P-value for T_cells vs Monocytes
P-value for  the test that non-synonymous rates differ between T_cells and Monocytes branches
P-value for Plasma vs Monocytes
P-value for  the test that non-synonymous rates differ between Plasma and Monocytes branches
Total branch length
The total length of branches contributing to inference at this site, and used to scale beta-alpha
